X-WR-CALDESC:365 verser ur Koranen\, en per dag. Med svensk och engelsk ö
 versättning\, originaltext på arabiska\, och en kort reflektion grundad 
 i klassisk tafsir. Sadaqah Jariyah från SalatTid.se
X-WR-CALNAME:Dagens vers 2026
X-PUBLISHED-TTL:P1D
X-WR-TIMEZONE:Europe/Stockholm
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Dagens vers (1:1): I GUDS\, DEN NÅDERIKES\, DEN BARMHÄRTIGES NAM
 N
DTSTART:20260501T090000
DTEND:20260501T091500
DTSTAMP:20260503T035720Z
UID:verse-001-2026-05-01@salattid.se
CATEGORIES:Vers,Daglig påminnelse,Beginnings
DESCRIPTION:Dagens vers: Quran 1:1\n\nI GUDS\, DEN NÅDERIKES\, DEN BARMH
 ÄRTIGES NAMN\n\n--------------------\nReflektion\nThe Basmalah opens 113 
 of the Quran's 114 surahs. To begin with His name is to acknowledge that n
 othing of consequence proceeds without Him. Al-Saadi notes that the singul
 ar word 'name' (ism) is general: it encompasses every one of His beautiful
  names\; every divine attribute is invoked when you say it. The two names 
 that follow\, al-Rahman (the vast mercy that encompasses all creation) and
  al-Rahim (the particular mercy promised to those who follow His messenger
 s)\, set the entire Quran's tone before its first lesson begins: God's rel
 ationship with you opens in mercy.\n\n--------------------\nSpråknyans\nA
 l-Zamakhshari devotes pages to a single grammatical question on this verse
 : what verb does the ba ('in/with') attach to? Bismillah literally reads '
 with the name of Allah\,' but what is the implicit verb? He argues for an 
 implicit verb that comes after 'the name of Allah\,' meaning the structure
  reads 'with the name of Allah\, I recite' rather than 'I recite with the 
 name of Allah.' Why? Because the worshipper's purpose is to give precedenc
 e to Allah's name. The grammar itself enacts the theology.\n\nOn al-Rahman
  vs al-Raheem: both come from the same root\, but al-Rahman is a more inte
 nsive form\, used only of Allah\; al-Raheem is more limited and can apply 
 to others. al-Rahman covers the great\, foundational mercies (creation\, s
 ustenance)\; al-Raheem then completes the picture: the subtle\, finer\, in
 timate mercies the first word didn't already imply.\n\n-------------------
 -\nEnglish\nIn the name of God\, the Lord of Mercy\, the Giver of Mercy!\n
 \n--------------------\nArabiska\nبِسْمِ اللَّهِ الرَّح
 ْمَٰنِ الرَّحِيمِ\n\n--------------------\nVarför denna v
 ers\nDay 1. The first verse of the Quran\, and the verse the Muslim recite
 s more than any other. Every meaningful beginning starts here.\n\n--------
 ------------\nKälla: Quran 1:1\nSalatTid.se - Sadaqah Jariyah\nhttps://sa
 lattid.com/verses
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://salattid.com/verses
BEGIN:VALARM
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Dagens vers (1:1): I GUDS\, DEN NÅDERIKES\, DEN BARMHÄRTIGES
  NAMN
TRIGGER:P0D
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
