BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Dagens vers (2:256): TVÅNG skall inte förekomma i trosfrågor. V
 ad som är rätt han
DTSTART:20260529T090000
DTEND:20260529T091500
DTSTAMP:20260503T035720Z
UID:verse-029-2026-05-29@salattid.se
CATEGORIES:Vers,Daglig påminnelse,Beginnings
DESCRIPTION:Dagens vers: Quran 2:256\n\nTVÅNG skall inte förekomma i tro
 sfrågor. Vad som är rätt handlande är nu klart skilt från fel och syn
 d. Den som förnekar de onda makterna och som tror på Gud\, har sannerlig
 en vunnit ett säkert fäste som aldrig ger vika. Gud hör allt\, vet allt
 .\n\n--------------------\nReflektion\nIbn Jarir records the asbab al-nuzu
 l from Ibn Abbas: before Islam\, when an Ansari woman could not bear child
 ren who survived\, she would vow that any surviving child would be raised 
 among the Jewish tribe of Banu al-Nadir. Years later\, when the Prophet (s
 aw) expelled Banu al-Nadir from Medina\, the Ansari parents whose children
  were among them tried to force the children to remain (and embrace Islam)
  rather than depart with the Jewish tribe. Allah revealed: 'There is no co
 mpulsion in religion. The right path has become distinct from error. Whoev
 er rejects taghut and believes in Allah has grasped the firmest handhold t
 hat will never break.' Ibn Kathir's gloss: 'Do not force anyone to become 
 Muslim\, for Islam is plain and clear\, and its proofs are evident\; whoev
 er Allah opens the heart to\, will embrace it with certainty.'\n\n--------
 ------------\nSpråknyans\nLa ikraha (no compulsion). The Arabic uses the 
 la al-nafiya li-l-jins construction: the absolute negation that denies the
  entire genus. Not 'do not compel' (a conditional command) but 'there is n
 o legitimate compulsion' (a categorical statement). Qad tabayyana ('has be
 come distinct'). The particle qad with the past tense intensifies the verb
 : 'has clearly become distinct.' Truth has been so plainly delineated from
  falsehood that the distinction is now perceptible to anyone who looks hon
 estly. Al-urwah al-wuthqa (the firmest handhold). Urwah is the loop or han
 dle of a vessel\, something you grip to carry or stabilize. Wuthqa is the 
 elative form of wathiq (firm\, secure). The metaphor: holding to faith in 
 Allah\, after rejecting taghut\, is like grasping the most secure handle t
 here is.\n\n--------------------\nEnglish\nThere is no compulsion in relig
 ion: true guidance has become distinct from error\, so whoever rejects fal
 se gods and believes in God has grasped the firmest hand-hold\, one that w
 ill never break. God is all hearing and all knowing.\n\n------------------
 --\nArabiska\nلَا إِكْرَاهَ فِي الدِّينِ ۖ قَد 
 تَّبَيَّنَ الرُّشْدُ مِنَ الْغَيِّ ۚ فَ
 مَن يَكْفُرْ بِالطَّاغُوتِ وَيُؤْمِن بِ
 اللَّهِ فَقَدِ اسْتَمْسَكَ بِالْعُرْوَ
 ةِ الْوُثْقَٰى لَا انفِصَامَ لَهَا ۗ وَا
 للَّهُ سَمِيعٌ عَلِيمٌ\n\n--------------------\nVarfö
 r denna vers\nThe Quran's central verse on religious non-coercion. Asbab a
 l-nuzul (Ibn Jarir): some Ansari parents had children being raised as Jews
 \; when Banu al-Nadir was being expelled from Medina\, the parents tried t
 o force their children to stay. Allah revealed: there is no compulsion in 
 religion.\n\n--------------------\nKälla: Quran 2:256\nSalatTid.se - Sada
 qah Jariyah\nhttps://salattid.com/verses
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://salattid.com/verses
BEGIN:VALARM
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Dagens vers (2:256): TVÅNG skall inte förekomma i trosfrågo
 r. Vad som är rätt han
TRIGGER:P0D
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
